snippet.textDisplay: I have a confession.  I saw the new C8 Corvette from a different light today.   I usually have to grow into liking a car, but this time I grew out of liking a car.  Sometimes down the line, maybe 3-5 years later I ask myself how I could have liked a car.  Today, I did that with the Corvette.  The Ferrari has a nice shape, the lambo has a nice shape.   This car looks like someone designed the front and someone designed the boxy back.  The boxy back takes a lot away for the asthetic.  Even though the sales will be great, because there are so many people excited about the redesign and all the power, lots of people will have the same negative feeling about the car.  It looks like a 2000 concept Corvette, this already aged.  I think it's the boxy back of the car that makes it look that way.  Don't get me wrong, it's gonna sell like crazy.
snippet.textOriginal: I have a confession.  I saw the new C8 Corvette from a different light today.   I usually have to grow into liking a car, but this time I grew out of liking a car.  Sometimes down the line, maybe 3-5 years later I ask myself how I could have liked a car.  Today, I did that with the Corvette.  The Ferrari has a nice shape, the lambo has a nice shape.   This car looks like someone designed the front and someone designed the boxy back.  The boxy back takes a lot away for the asthetic.  Even though the sales will be great, because there are so many people excited about the redesign and all the power, lots of people will have the same negative feeling about the car.  It looks like a 2000 concept Corvette, this already aged.  I think it's the boxy back of the car that makes it look that way.  Don't get me wrong, it's gonna sell like crazy.

snippet.textDisplay: The C8's specs and price are very close to the Model 3 performance version (which also has a track mode). Its automation (like remembering curbs to elevate suspension) have long been in Model S & X (which are about the same price as optioned versions of the C8, but offer 2.3s 0-60).   The C8 is impressive, so why not compare it to its real competition?

snippet.textDisplay:
Just a FYI....
GM, in deciding to select Nevada as it’s test location for journalists is a controlled environment setting. And I’m focusing my attention to the comment about the base suspension could possibly be enough for daily commutes.
Out West, Southwest and South I absolutely agree. But from the Midwest all the way to Maine to the East, I’m not so sure if the base suspension would be the best option. The base suspension would be tested on the roads in Michigan for sure. But I can’t wait to see real environment driving to sort out the quality of the suspension setup.
